5:T4b8,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"SoftwareApplication","@id":"https://www.xrnotify.io/#app","name":"XRNotify","description":"Real-time webhook notification platform for the XRP Ledger.","url":"https://www.xrnotify.io","applicationCategory":"DeveloperApplication","operatingSystem":"Web","offers":[{"@type":"Offer","name":"Free","price":"0","priceCurrency":"USD","description":"1,000 events/month, 2 webhooks"},{"@type":"Offer","name":"Starter","price":"29.00","priceCurrency":"USD","description":"50,000 events/month, 10 webhooks, WebSocket access"},{"@type":"Offer","name":"Pro","price":"99.00","priceCurrency":"USD","description":"500,000 events/month, 50 webhooks, priority delivery"}],"creator":{"@id":"https://www.jonomor.com/ali-morgan#person"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://www.jonomor.com/#organization"},"isPartOf":{"@id":"https://www.jonomor.com/#organization"},"featureList":["Real-time XRPL event ingestion","HMAC-SHA256 signed webhook delivery","Automatic retries with exponential backoff","Dead-letter queue for failed deliveries","Event replay and reprocessing","23+ XRPL event types supported","Developer dashboard with delivery logs","Per-webhook filtering by event type and account"]}6:Tcff,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","@id":"https://www.xrnotify.io/#faqpage","name":"XRNotify FAQ — Common Questions About XRPL Webhooks","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is XRNotify?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify is a real-time webhook notification platform for the XRP Ledger. It monitors XRPL transactions as they confirm on-chain, normalizes them into clean JSON schemas, and delivers them to your endpoints via HMAC-signed HTTPS POST requests. XRNotify eliminates the need to run your own XRPL node or build polling infrastructure."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What XRPL events does XRNotify support?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify supports 23+ event types across all major XRPL transaction categories: payments (XRP and issued tokens), NFT operations (minting, burning, offers, transfers), DEX trades (OfferCreate, OfferCancel, AMM operations), trustline changes (TrustSet), escrow events (create, finish, cancel), check operations, and account-level changes like settings modifications and deletions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does webhook delivery work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"When an XRPL transaction matches your configured filters, XRNotify normalizes the event, signs the payload with your webhook secret using HMAC-SHA256, and delivers it as an HTTPS POST to your endpoint. If delivery fails, XRNotify retries with exponential backoff (up to 10 attempts over 12 hours). Events that exhaust all retries are moved to a dead-letter queue for manual inspection and replay."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is XRNotify free?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify offers a free tier with 1,000 events per month and 2 webhook endpoints — enough for testing and hobby projects. Paid plans start at $29/month (Starter: 50,000 events, 10 webhooks, WebSocket streaming) and $99/month (Pro: 500,000 events, 50 webhooks, priority delivery). Enterprise plans with custom SLAs are available on request."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I verify webhook signatures?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Every XRNotify webhook includes an X-XRNotify-Signature header containing an HMAC-SHA256 hash of the request body, computed using your webhook signing secret. To verify, compute the HMAC-SHA256 of the raw request body with your secret and compare it to the header value using a constant-time comparison function to prevent timing attacks."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Who built XRNotify?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify was built by Ali Morgan, founder of Jonomor, a systems architecture studio focused on AI Visibility and real-time infrastructure intelligence. XRNotify is the XRPL instrumentation layer of the Jonomor ecosystem, which also includes Guard-Clause, MyPropOps, The Neutral Bridge, Evenfield, and H.U.N.I.E."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is XRNotify part of a larger ecosystem?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. XRNotify is part of the Jonomor ecosystem, a suite of interconnected software products built by Ali Morgan. Within the ecosystem, XRNotify serves as the real-time observation layer — detecting XRPL events at the point of origin before they flow through interpretation and operational layers in other Jonomor properties."}}]}0:["pQjrRFT3j-NbWRfetFzsE",[[["",{"children":["docs",{"children":["reference",{"children":["event-schema",{"children":["__PAGE__",{}]}]}]}]},"$undefined","$undefined",true],["",{"children":["docs",{"children":["reference",{"children":["event-schema",{"children":["__PAGE__",{},[["$L1",["$","div",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0f] text-white antialiased","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"border-b border-zinc-800/50","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-2 text-sm","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/docs","className":"text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-300 no-underline","children":"Docs"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-zinc-600","children":"/"}],["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/docs#reference","className":"text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-300 no-underline","children":"Reference"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-zinc-600","children":"/"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300","children":"Event Schema"}]]}],["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/dashboard","className":"text-zinc-400 hover:text-white transition-colors text-sm no-underline","children":"Dashboard →"}]]}]}],["$","main",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block text-xs font-medium text-emerald-400 bg-emerald-500/10 border border-emerald-500/20 rounded px-2 py-0.5 mb-4","children":"Reference"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-3","children":"Event Schema"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-lg leading-relaxed","children":["Every event delivered by XRNotify follows a canonical top-level structure. The event-type-specific data lives inside the ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400","children":"payload"}]," field."]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Overview"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["Regardless of whether the event is a payment, NFT mint, DEX trade, or any other activity, the outer envelope is identical. This makes it straightforward to write a single parsing layer and then branch on"," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"event_type"}]," to reach type-specific payload handling."]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":["Events are delivered as HTTP POST requests with a"," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"Content-Type: application/json"}]," header and a signed body. Always verify the ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"X-XRNotify-Signature"}]," header before trusting the payload."]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"TypeScript interface"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"interface XRNotifyEvent<T = Record<string, unknown>> {\n  /** Unique event identifier in format xrpl:<ledger>:<txhash>:<type>[:<idx>] */\n  event_id: string;\n\n  /** Event type string (e.g. \"payment.xrp\", \"nft.minted\") */\n  event_type: EventType;\n\n  /** XRPL ledger index this event occurred in */\n  ledger_index: number;\n\n  /** ISO 8601 timestamp of ledger close */\n  timestamp: string;\n\n  /** Network: \"mainnet\" | \"testnet\" | \"devnet\" */\n  network: string;\n\n  /** The webhook that triggered this delivery */\n  webhook_id: string;\n\n  /** Event-type-specific payload */\n  payload: T;\n}"}]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Field descriptions"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"overflow-x-auto","children":["$","table",null,{"className":"w-full text-sm border-collapse","children":[["$","thead",null,{"children":["$","tr",null,{"className":"border-b border-zinc-800","children":[["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-400 font-medium","children":"Field"}],["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-400 font-medium","children":"Type"}],["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left py-2 text-zinc-400 font-medium","children":"Description"}]]}]}],["$","tbody",null,{"className":"divide-y divide-zinc-800/50","children":[["$","tr","event_id",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 text-xs","children":"event_id"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-xs","children":"string"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300 text-xs leading-relaxed","children":"Globally unique, deterministic ID. Format: xrpl:<ledger>:<txhash>:<type>[:<idx>]"}]]}],["$","tr","event_type",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 text-xs","children":"event_type"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-xs","children":"string"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300 text-xs leading-relaxed","children":"One of the 23 supported event types (see EventType union below)"}]]}],["$","tr","ledger_index",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 text-xs","children":"ledger_index"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-xs","children":"number"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300 text-xs leading-relaxed","children":"XRPL ledger sequence number in which the transaction was validated"}]]}],["$","tr","timestamp",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 text-xs","children":"timestamp"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-xs","children":"string"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300 text-xs leading-relaxed","children":"ISO 8601 datetime, always UTC, matching the ledger close time"}]]}],["$","tr","network",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 text-xs","children":"network"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-xs","children":"string"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300 text-xs leading-relaxed","children":"Always \"mainnet\" for production. \"testnet\" or \"devnet\" for test webhooks"}]]}],["$","tr","webhook_id",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 text-xs","children":"webhook_id"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-xs","children":"string"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300 text-xs leading-relaxed","children":"wh_ prefixed ID of the webhook that triggered this delivery"}]]}],["$","tr","payload",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 text-xs","children":"payload"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-xs","children":"object"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300 text-xs leading-relaxed","children":"Event-type-specific fields. Schema varies by event_type"}]]}]]}]]}]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":["The ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400","children":"event_id"}]," format"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":["Event IDs are deterministically generated from on-chain data, so the same ledger event always produces the same ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"event_id"}],". This makes them safe to use as idempotency keys in your processing layer."]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"# Pattern:\nxrpl:<ledger_index>:<tx_hash>:<event_type>[:<sub_index>]\n\n# Examples:\nxrpl:84512701:A1B2C3D4E5F6...1234:payment.xrp\nxrpl:84512705:F6E5D4C3B2A1...5678:nft.offer_accepted\nxrpl:84512710:123456789ABC...ABCD:dex.offer_partial:0\nxrpl:84512710:123456789ABC...ABCD:dex.offer_partial:1"}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":["The optional ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":":sub_index"}]," suffix appears when a single transaction generates multiple events of the same type (e.g., a single DEX trade filling multiple offers). Each resulting event gets a unique numeric index."]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":[["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400","children":"EventType"}]," union (all 23 values)"]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"type EventType =\n  // Payments\n  | 'payment.xrp'\n  | 'payment.issued'\n\n  // NFTs\n  | 'nft.minted'\n  | 'nft.burned'\n  | 'nft.offer_created'\n  | 'nft.offer_accepted'\n  | 'nft.offer_cancelled'\n\n  // DEX\n  | 'dex.offer_created'\n  | 'dex.offer_cancelled'\n  | 'dex.offer_filled'\n  | 'dex.offer_partial'\n\n  // Trustlines\n  | 'trustline.created'\n  | 'trustline.modified'\n  | 'trustline.deleted'\n\n  // Accounts\n  | 'account.created'\n  | 'account.deleted'\n  | 'account.settings_changed'\n\n  // Escrows\n  | 'escrow.created'\n  | 'escrow.finished'\n  | 'escrow.cancelled'\n\n  // Checks\n  | 'check.created'\n  | 'check.cashed'\n  | 'check.cancelled';"}]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Sample event (payment.xrp)"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"{\n  \"event_id\": \"xrpl:84512701:A1B2C3D4E5F67890ABCDEF1234567890ABCDEF1234567890ABCDEF12345678:payment.xrp\",\n  \"event_type\": \"payment.xrp\",\n  \"ledger_index\": 84512701,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T14:23:07Z\",\n  \"network\": \"mainnet\",\n  \"webhook_id\": \"wh_abc123def456\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"sender\": \"rN7n3473SaZBCG4dFL75SqSGPpvNRRBXtK\",\n    \"receiver\": \"rPT1Sjq2YGrBMTttX4GZHjKu9dyfzbpAYe\",\n    \"amount\": \"25000000\",\n    \"destination_tag\": 1042,\n    \"tx_hash\": \"A1B2C3D4E5F67890ABCDEF1234567890ABCDEF1234567890ABCDEF12345678\"\n  }\n}"}]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"JSON Schema (top-level envelope)"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":["Use this schema to validate inbound webhook bodies with any JSON Schema v2020-12 compatible validator (e.g., ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"ajv"}]," in Node.js)."]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"{\n  \"$schema\": \"https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema\",\n  \"$id\": \"https://www.xrnotify.io/schemas/event.json\",\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"required\": [\n    \"event_id\",\n    \"event_type\",\n    \"ledger_index\",\n    \"timestamp\",\n    \"network\",\n    \"webhook_id\",\n    \"payload\"\n  ],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"event_id\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"pattern\": \"^xrpl:\\\\d+:[A-F0-9]+:[a-z.]+(?::\\\\d+)?$\"\n    },\n    \"event_type\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\"\n    },\n    \"ledger_index\": {\n      \"type\": \"integer\",\n      \"minimum\": 1\n    },\n    \"timestamp\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"format\": \"date-time\"\n    },\n    \"network\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"enum\": [\"mainnet\", \"testnet\", \"devnet\"]\n    },\n    \"webhook_id\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"pattern\": \"^wh_\"\n    },\n    \"payload\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"additionalProperties\": false\n}"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-emerald-500/10 border border-emerald-500/20 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-zinc-300","children":["Payload schemas for each event type — including all field names, types, and optional fields — are documented in the"," ",["$","$L2",n